<ul><li>Vivaha Sanskara, The Hindu Wedding Ceremony, <a href="/wiki/OCLC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="OCLC (identifier)">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/772457120">772457120</a> and <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-9793501-3-1" title="Special:BookSources/0-9793501-3-1">0-9793501-3-1</a> and OpenLibrary <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://openlibrary.org/works/OL16793722W%7COL16793722W">OL16793722W</a></li>
<li>Kavita Kapoor (2007), Rituals &amp; customs of a Hindu wedding&#160;: design &amp; planning guide, <a href="/wiki/OCLC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="OCLC (identifier)">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/225099749">225099749</a>, <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1434319272" title="Special:BookSources/978-1434319272">978-1434319272</a></li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFMichaels2004" class="citation cs2">Michaels, A (2004), <i>Hinduism: Past and Present</i> (5th&#160;ed.), Princeton University Press Oracle, pp.&#160;111–131, <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-691-08953-1" title="Special:BookSources/0-691-08953-1"><bdi>0-691-08953-1</bdi></a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Hinduism%3A+Past+and+Present&amp;rft.pages=111-131&amp;rft.edition=5th&amp;rft.pub=Princeton+University+Press+Oracle&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.isbn=0-691-08953-1&amp;rft.aulast=Michaels&amp;rft.aufirst=A&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHindu+wedding" class="Z3988"></span></li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFWorld_Hindu_Council_of_America_(VHPA)2011" class="citation cs2">World Hindu Council of America (VHPA) (2011), <i>Vivāha Saṃskāra: the Hindu wedding ceremony</i>, Indianapolis, USA: Bhar Printing, Inc., <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0979350139" title="Special:BookSources/978-0979350139"><bdi>978-0979350139</bdi></a>, <a href="/wiki/OCLC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="OCLC (identifier)">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/772457120">772457120</a>, <a href="/wiki/OL_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="OL (identifier)">OL</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://openlibrary.org/books/OL25414013M">25414013M</a>, 0979350131</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Viv%C4%81ha+Sa%E1%B9%83sk%C4%81ra%3A+the+Hindu+wedding+ceremony&amp;rft.place=Indianapolis%2C+USA&amp;rft.pub=Bhar+Printing%2C+Inc.&amp;rft.date=2011&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F772457120&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fopenlibrary.org%2Fbooks%2FOL25414013M%23id-name%3DOL&amp;rft.isbn=978-0979350139&amp;rft.au=World+Hindu+Council+of+America+%28VHPA%29&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHindu+wedding" class="Z3988"></span></li>
